\sum_{m,n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{(m+n)!}=\sum_{k=2}^\infty\left(\sum_{m+n=k}\frac{1}{(m+n)!}\right) = \sum_{k=2}^\infty\left(\sum_{m+n=k}\frac{1}{k!}\right) =\sum_{k=2}^\infty \left(\frac{1}{k!}\left(\sum_{m+n=k}1\right)\right)
\sum_{m,n=1}^\infty\frac{1}{(m+n)!}=\sum_{k=2}^\infty\sum_{\array{m+n=k\\m,n\geq 1}}\frac{1}{k!} = \sum_{k=2}^\infty\frac{k-1}{k!}\leq\sum_{k=2}^\infty \frac{k(k-1)}{k!}=\sum_{k=2}^\infty \frac{1}{(k-2)!}<\infty
